1
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:39,712
and so shall be saved
from mine enemies !

2
00:01:40,760 --> 00:01:44,639
The waves of death
have closed about me !

3
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:48,950
The cords of hell
have encompassed me about

4
00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:53,356
and the snares of death
have overtaken me !

5
00:01:54,040 --> 00:01:56,998
The cords of hell
have encompassed me about

6
00:01:57,480 --> 00:02:01,917
and the snares of death
have overtaken me !

7
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:08,149
ln my tribulation l call to the Lord
and cry to my God

8
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:12,193
and He heard my voice
cry out His temple ... !

9
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:14,635
Move back ! Clear the way !

10
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:16,916
Move back !

11
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:21,156
Keep in line, woman !

12
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:32,149
By order of their gracious Majesties,
Queen Mary and King Philip,

13
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:36,950
we are come to witness the burning
of these Protestant heretics

14
00:02:37,040 --> 00:02:42,034
who have denied the authority
of the one true Catholic church

15
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:44,873
and of His Holiness the Pope.

16
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:50,909
Let them burn for all eternity
in the flames of hell.

17
00:02:55,560 --> 00:03:01,396
Benedicat te Omnipotens Deus Pater,
Filius et Spiritus Sanctus.

18
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:07,034
Benedicat te Omnipotens Deus Pater,
Filius et Spiritus Sanctus.

19
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:13,479
Benedicat te Omnipotens Deus Pater,
Filius et Spiritus Sanctus.

20
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:15,596
God bless you, Master Ridley !

21
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:19,434
For the love of God, friends, help me !
l burn too slowly !

22
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:24,675
Help them !
For God's sake, help them !

23
00:04:25,320 --> 00:04:27,993
Your Grace, the Queen is with child.

24
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:32,676
They should've consulted me
before they rang the bells.

25
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:38,196
ls it true ?

26
00:04:38,280 --> 00:04:43,513
She has ceased to bleed, her breasts have
some milk, and her stomach is swollen.

27
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:44,874
ls it true ?

28
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:49,238
The King has not shared her bed
for many months.

29
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:53,233
He has a repugnance for it,
as lately Your Grace has for mine.

30
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:14,278
Norfolk...

31
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:18,391
Your Majesties,
this is most wondrous news.

32
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:19,913
lndeed.

33
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:24,391
We do thank God for this,
our most happy condition.

34
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:26,914
We must also thank His Majesty
for this event

35
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:29,389
which is nothing short of a miracle.

36
00:05:32,760 --> 00:05:37,038
What news, my Lords,
of the rebellion against our authority ?

37
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:39,638
Sussex ?

38
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:42,996
Madam, it is safely dispatched,
thanks to His Grace.

39
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:46,834
Sir Thomas Wyatt and the other leaders
are already dealt with.

40
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:50,833
lf they had succeeded,
these Protestants and heretics

41
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:52,911
meant to place your sister

42
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:55,036
upon the throne.

43
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:59,836
There is no proof
against the Lady Elizabeth.

44
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:03,310
- She is plainly guilty.
- What need is there of proof ?

45
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:06,358
lf she remains alive,
there will be plots to raise her

46
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:08,078
to the throne.

47
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:09,115
Ambassador ?

48
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:15,196
l agree with His Grace.

49
00:06:15,280 --> 00:06:19,353
She is a heretic.
She must never be allowed to succeed.

50
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:20,714
But if she...

51
00:06:21,760 --> 00:06:24,593
lf she were brought properly to trial,

52
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:27,194
she would not be found guilty,

53
00:06:27,280 --> 00:06:30,033
and we would be condemned.
She has friends in Parliament.

54
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:33,635
My sister was born
of that whore Anne Boleyn !

55
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:37,474
She was born a bastard !
She will never rule England !

56
00:06:44,880 --> 00:06:49,954
Your Grace will find some proof
of her treachery. l am most sure of it.

57
00:07:29,640 --> 00:07:31,198
lt was so fast !

58
00:07:45,440 --> 00:07:47,396
May l join you, my Lady ?

59
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:58,196
lf it please you, sir.

60
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:13,393
My Lady !

61
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:14,833
My Lady !

62
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:26,398
Princess Elizabeth !

63
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:42,356
Princess Elizabeth !

64
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:52,311
You are accused of conspiring
with Sir Thomas Wyatt

65
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:54,960
against Her Sovereign Majesty

66
00:09:55,040 --> 00:09:57,600
and are arrested for treason.

67
00:09:57,680 --> 00:10:03,038
l am commanded to take you hence
from this place... to the Tower.

68
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:17,916
Remember who you are.

69
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:28,436
Do not be afraid of them.

70
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:34,596
My Lady.

71
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,956
Prisoner to the steps.

72
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:26,155
l cannot confess to something
l did not do.

73
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:27,593
Your denials are in vain.

74
00:11:27,680 --> 00:11:31,832
You knew of the rebellion, Madam.
lt is plain enough.

75
00:11:31,920 --> 00:11:33,592
Where is your proof ?

76
00:11:33,680 --> 00:11:35,716
lt was to your advantage.

77
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:37,756
You must let me see the Queen...

78
00:11:37,840 --> 00:11:40,957
You despise the Queen,
and the Catholic faith.

79
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:51,995
l am a true and faithful subject.

80
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:54,758
l attend Mass...

81
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:57,274
You pretend ! But in your heart...

82
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:02,949
What's that ? What say you, Madam ?

83
00:12:03,040 --> 00:12:04,678
Speak up !

84
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:08,878
Madam, if there is some small truth
in these charges,

85
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:12,430
however innocently or unknowingly
you did proceed,

86
00:12:12,520 --> 00:12:14,476
you had best confess.

87
00:12:14,560 --> 00:12:16,232
l ask you

88
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:20,950
why we must tear ourselves apart
for this small question of religion.

89
00:12:21,040 --> 00:12:23,031
Catholic, Protestant... !

90
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:26,908
You think it small,
though it killed your mother !

91
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:38,158
We all...

92
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:42,800
We all believe in God, my Lords.

93
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:46,668
No, Madam,
there is only one true belief.

94
00:12:46,760 --> 00:12:48,830
The other - heresy.

95
00:13:16,560 --> 00:13:18,516
Madam, you are cold.

96
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:21,034
l do not need your pity.

97
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:23,231
Accept it, then,

98
00:13:23,320 --> 00:13:24,833
for my sake.

99
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:29,872
Thank you.

100
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:33,520
l shall not forget this kindness.

101
00:14:42,480 --> 00:14:44,630
Tonight l think l die.

102
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:53,476
Madam.

103
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:57,792
No... !

104
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:12,155
Save me ! Save me !

105
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:48,436
l am Your Majesty's most humble servant.

106
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:05,517
Come here.

107
00:16:06,680 --> 00:16:09,240
Closer, so l might see your face.

108
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:20,156
When l look at you
l see nothing of the King.

109
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:23,038
Only that whore - your mother.

110
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:29,994
My father never did anything so well
as to cut off her head.

111
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:33,072
Your Majesty forgets
he was also my father.

112
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:39,995
Why will you not confess
your crimes against me ?

113
00:16:40,080 --> 00:16:43,197
Because, Your Majesty,
l have committed none.

114
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:48,160
You speak with such sincerity !

115
00:16:48,560 --> 00:16:51,950
l see you are still a consummate actress.

116
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:56,475
My husband is gone.

117
00:16:56,560 --> 00:16:59,120
They have poisoned my child.

118
00:17:00,480 --> 00:17:02,835
They say it is a tumour.

119
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:06,436
Madam, you are not well.

120
00:17:06,520 --> 00:17:10,479
They say this cancer
will make you Queen, but they are wrong !

121
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:14,838
Look there ! lt is your death warrant.
All l need do is sign it.

122
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:20,153
Mary, if you sign that paper,
you will be murdering your own sister.

123
00:17:25,640 --> 00:17:28,200
You will promise me something ?

124
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:34,559
When l am gone, you will
do everything in your power

125
00:17:34,640 --> 00:17:36,870
to uphold the Catholic faith.

126
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:42,910
Do not take away from the people
the consolations of the Blessed Virgin.

127
00:17:46,040 --> 00:17:47,996
When l am Queen

128
00:17:48,520 --> 00:17:50,476
l promise

129
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:55,833
to act as my conscience dictates.

130
00:17:58,320 --> 00:18:00,550
Well, do not think to be Queen at all.

131
00:18:00,640 --> 00:18:03,837
You may return to your house at Hatfield,

132
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:07,196
but you will remain under arrest
until l am recovered.

133
00:18:08,960 --> 00:18:10,916
Thank you, Your Majesty.

134
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:12,353
No...

135
00:18:12,440 --> 00:18:17,309
Feed her to the wolves.
Let her see what they are like.

136
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:05,959
She is just a child,
and yet still you piss yourselves !

137
00:19:09,240 --> 00:19:12,232
Your Grace,
Protestants are returning from abroad.

138
00:19:12,320 --> 00:19:17,269
Yes, and have made plans to massacre
every Catholic in England.

139
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:21,753
There would be butchery indeed
if such a plan were even conceivable.

140
00:19:21,840 --> 00:19:24,115
They say Walsingham
will return from France.

141
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:26,156
Walsingham is nothing !

142
00:19:33,360 --> 00:19:35,476
Be sure he does not.

143
00:19:35,560 --> 00:19:40,190
There is so little beauty in this world,
and so much suffering.

144
00:19:42,080 --> 00:19:45,038
Do you suppose
that is what God had in mind ?

145
00:19:46,120 --> 00:19:48,873
That is to say, if there is a God at all.

146
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:54,077
Perhaps there is nothing
in this universe but ourselves

147
00:19:55,040 --> 00:19:56,996
and our thoughts.

148
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:06,116
Think before you do this.

149
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:17,709
lf you must do it,

150
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:19,756
then do it now.

151
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:23,115
And without regret.

152
00:20:23,200 --> 00:20:25,270
But first think carefully

153
00:20:28,640 --> 00:20:30,596
and be certain

154
00:20:30,760 --> 00:20:32,716
why it needs to be done.

155
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:41,796
Come here.

156
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:53,916
Look out there.

157
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:57,680
There is a whole world waiting for you.

158
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:03,559
lnnocence
is the most precious thing you possess.

159
00:21:04,440 --> 00:21:07,398
Lose that and you lose your soul.

160
00:21:22,520 --> 00:21:23,919
..et Spiritus Sancti...

161
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:25,069
Amen.

162
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:26,718
Father...

163
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:29,234
- Sir William !
- My Lady...

164
00:21:29,320 --> 00:21:32,471
There was nowhere else
we could meet in safety.

165
00:21:32,560 --> 00:21:34,710
Listen to me carefully.

166
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:37,030
All things move in our favour.

167
00:21:37,120 --> 00:21:40,510
Many of our friends
are returning from exile.

168
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:43,831
But these are most uncertain times

169
00:21:43,920 --> 00:21:46,150
and your life remains in danger.

170
00:21:46,240 --> 00:21:48,708
You must therefore say nothing

171
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:52,349
and meet no-one
whose visit may compromise you.

172
00:21:52,440 --> 00:21:53,668
No-one ?

173
00:21:53,760 --> 00:21:56,513
No-one. Not even Lord Robert.

174
00:21:56,600 --> 00:22:01,913
- But he is a trusted friend.
- Child, listen to me. Please.

175
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:05,879
You are most innocent
in the ways of this world

176
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:07,951
and we must do all we may

177
00:22:08,040 --> 00:22:11,032
to guarantee the security of your throne.

178
00:22:11,120 --> 00:22:14,112
Now there is someone
l do wish you to meet.

179
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:17,351
Monseigneur Alvaro de la Quadra,
the Spanish Ambassador.

180
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:18,429
Why do l...

181
00:22:22,480 --> 00:22:24,232
My Lady,

182
00:22:24,320 --> 00:22:27,357
l bring a message.

183
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:32,230
The King of Spain is enraptured,
and offers you his hand in marriage.

184
00:22:32,320 --> 00:22:34,709
My sister is not yet dead.

185
00:22:34,800 --> 00:22:36,950
Her bed is still warm.

186
00:22:37,520 --> 00:22:40,273
His Majesty finds it already cold.

187
00:22:52,720 --> 00:22:54,676
You must sign it.

188
00:22:54,760 --> 00:22:57,911
For the love of God, sign it.

189
00:23:01,120 --> 00:23:04,078
Will you leave your kingdom to a heretic ?

190
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:14,239
He then said that this King
would marry me

191
00:23:14,320 --> 00:23:18,711
but would not expect to share my bed
more than two or three times a year.

192
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:20,392
As much as that ?

193
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:25,032
Well, he...

194
00:23:25,120 --> 00:23:26,917
He is enraptured.

195
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:27,955
Naturally.

196
00:23:30,360 --> 00:23:34,148
But... his affairs would otherwise
keep him in Spain.

197
00:23:35,800 --> 00:23:37,950
Then the King is a fool.

198
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:45,599
What could ever be important enough
to keep him from your bed ?

199
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:57,193
Robert,

200
00:23:57,280 --> 00:23:59,555
you should not say such things.

201
00:23:59,640 --> 00:24:01,596
Then l shall only think them.

202
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:11,237
Everything is so uncertain !
Sir William says my life is still in danger.

203
00:24:11,320 --> 00:24:14,835
Do not listen to everything he tells you.
Do not listen to any of them.

204
00:24:14,920 --> 00:24:16,558
None of them are of consequence.

205
00:24:16,640 --> 00:24:20,553
- When you are Queen...
- l am not... l am not Queen yet.

206
00:24:20,640 --> 00:24:22,517
You will be.

207
00:24:22,600 --> 00:24:24,238
Elizabeth,

208
00:24:24,320 --> 00:24:26,197
Queen of England.

209
00:24:27,280 --> 00:24:29,589
A court to worship you.

210
00:24:29,680 --> 00:24:31,671
A country to obey you.

211
00:24:31,760 --> 00:24:34,558
Poems written celebrating your beauty.

212
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:39,111
Music composed in your honour,
and they will be nothing to you.

213
00:24:39,960 --> 00:24:41,916
l will mean nothing to you.

214
00:24:46,840 --> 00:24:49,274
How could you ever be nothing to me ?

215
00:24:52,360 --> 00:24:55,318
Robert, you know
you are everything to me.

216
00:24:56,080 --> 00:24:58,036
All that l am

217
00:24:58,120 --> 00:25:00,076
it is you.

218
00:25:06,320 --> 00:25:06,593
Benedicta tu in mulieribus

219
00:25:08,480 --> 00:25:12,439
et benedictus fructus ventris tui, lesus.

220
00:25:13,320 --> 00:25:15,276
Sancta Maria, Mater Dei

221
00:25:16,360 --> 00:25:19,318
ora pro nobis peccatoribus, nunc...

222
00:25:23,680 --> 00:25:25,636
ls she dead ?

223
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:46,236
Give it to her.

224
00:26:11,680 --> 00:26:13,193
My Lady...

225
00:26:17,080 --> 00:26:19,435
The Earl of Sussex is here.

226
00:27:08,560 --> 00:27:10,516
The Queen is dead !

227
00:27:10,960 --> 00:27:12,916
Long live the Queen !

228
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:17,716
Long live the Queen !

229
00:27:25,040 --> 00:27:27,270
This is the Lord's doing

230
00:27:29,040 --> 00:27:34,592
and it is marvellous in our eyes.

231
00:27:37,680 --> 00:27:40,513
To the north, l present unto you

232
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:43,512
Elizabeth, your undoubted Queen !

233
00:27:45,920 --> 00:27:48,070
To the south, l present to you

234
00:27:48,160 --> 00:27:50,913
Elizabeth, your undoubted Queen !

235
00:29:05,160 --> 00:29:07,116
l crown thee Elizabeth,

236
00:29:07,880 --> 00:29:12,829
Queen of England, lreland and France.

237
00:29:44,040 --> 00:29:46,395
God save Your Majesty.

238
00:29:50,920 --> 00:29:56,438
Your Majesty has inherited
a most parlous and degenerate state.

239
00:29:56,520 --> 00:29:59,876
lt's threatened from abroad
by France and Spain

240
00:29:59,960 --> 00:30:03,270
and is weaker in men, monies and riches

241
00:30:03,360 --> 00:30:05,237
than l have ever known it.

242
00:30:05,320 --> 00:30:06,753
What are you saying ?

243
00:30:06,840 --> 00:30:10,992
Madam, your treasury is empty.
The Navy is run-down,

244
00:30:11,080 --> 00:30:14,231
there is no standing army,
and no munitions.

245
00:30:14,320 --> 00:30:18,472
There is not a fortress
that could withstand a single shot.

246
00:30:18,560 --> 00:30:22,314
- l have no desire for war, sir.
- But that is not the end of it.

247
00:30:22,400 --> 00:30:25,995
Here at home there are those
who wish Your Majesty ill.

248
00:30:26,080 --> 00:30:30,073
Mary of Scots has already
laid claim to your throne,

249
00:30:30,160 --> 00:30:31,991
and Norfolk...

250
00:30:32,080 --> 00:30:34,958
Norfolk covets it relentlessly.

251
00:30:35,040 --> 00:30:39,397
Madam, until you marry
and produce an heir,

252
00:30:40,240 --> 00:30:42,800
you will find no security.

253
00:30:57,200 --> 00:30:59,156
That's Sir Christopher Hatton.

254
00:31:10,760 --> 00:31:12,910
- There is Sir William Makepeace...
- l do not see...

255
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:14,399
- Lord Ensley, Your Majesty.
- Delighted.

256
00:31:14,480 --> 00:31:17,870
l do not see why a woman
need marry at all.

257
00:31:31,040 --> 00:31:33,235
Come on, come on !

258
00:31:34,440 --> 00:31:36,396
This is Mistress Quickly.

259
00:31:51,520 --> 00:31:55,354
You will recall His Excellency
the Spanish Ambassador.

260
00:31:55,440 --> 00:31:57,396
How could l forget ?

261
00:31:57,480 --> 00:31:58,435
Excellency.

262
00:31:58,520 --> 00:32:00,476
Your Majesty.

263
00:32:04,680 --> 00:32:06,352
He's French. You'll have to speak up.

264
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:16,956
Do l know that gentleman ?

265
00:32:17,480 --> 00:32:22,156
That is Sir Francis Walsingham, Madam.
He has returned from exile

266
00:32:22,240 --> 00:32:26,472
and l have appointed him
to have a care for Your Majesty's person.

267
00:32:33,360 --> 00:32:35,112
Ah !

268
00:32:35,400 --> 00:32:36,913
Excellency...

269
00:32:38,400 --> 00:32:39,355
Majesty...

270
00:32:45,320 --> 00:32:50,348
May l present the French Ambassador,
His Excellency Monsieur de Foix.

271
00:32:50,440 --> 00:32:52,158
Your Excellency.

272
00:32:53,800 --> 00:32:57,759
l suppose the French
do offer some suitor to her.

273
00:32:57,840 --> 00:32:59,671
Naturally.

274
00:32:59,760 --> 00:33:03,594
Everything now depends
upon the husband that woman takes.

275
00:33:03,680 --> 00:33:05,750
King Henry of Anjou
sends you brotherly love.

276
00:33:05,840 --> 00:33:11,392
He trusts the relationship between
our countries may be much improved.

277
00:33:11,480 --> 00:33:12,799
That is also my hope.

278
00:33:12,880 --> 00:33:17,635
The King expects that you will
consider the suit of his brother,

279
00:33:17,720 --> 00:33:20,109
the Duke of Anjou.

280
00:33:20,200 --> 00:33:23,875
Her Majesty will consider
the proposal most carefully.

281
00:33:27,080 --> 00:33:31,710
lt is unfortunate, however,
that the Duke's aunt, Mary of Guise,

282
00:33:31,800 --> 00:33:35,190
chooses to garrison Scotland
with French troops.

283
00:33:39,040 --> 00:33:40,393
Ladies...

284
00:33:44,560 --> 00:33:50,032
The marriage of a Queen, Excellency,
is born of politics, not childish passion.

285
00:33:58,320 --> 00:33:59,435
Your Grace.

286
00:33:59,520 --> 00:34:01,476
Walsingham !

287
00:34:04,160 --> 00:34:06,116
Welcome to England.

288
00:34:06,200 --> 00:34:08,873
- Your Grace is surprised ?
- No.

289
00:34:08,960 --> 00:34:10,951
Only a little disappointed.

290
00:34:54,040 --> 00:34:55,996
Play a volta !

291
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:50,719
When may l see you in private ?

292
00:35:52,040 --> 00:35:53,075
ln private ?

293
00:35:54,600 --> 00:35:56,556
Have you forgot, my Lord ?

294
00:35:57,800 --> 00:35:59,552
l am Queen now.

295
00:36:18,320 --> 00:36:19,639
He's coming.

296
00:36:19,720 --> 00:36:20,835
He's coming !

297
00:36:33,720 --> 00:36:35,631
My Ladies.

298
00:36:35,720 --> 00:36:37,676
My Lord.

299
00:36:39,680 --> 00:36:42,752
You blush, Lady Knollys.

300
00:36:42,840 --> 00:36:44,956
Are you in love ?

301
00:36:45,040 --> 00:36:46,632
No, my Lord.

302
00:36:46,720 --> 00:36:49,678
Then you should be,
or waste all that beauty.

303
00:36:58,760 --> 00:37:00,716
Does Her Majesty sleep ?

304
00:37:01,360 --> 00:37:03,316
Not yet, Sir William.

305
00:37:03,400 --> 00:37:05,550
She is... overwrought.

306
00:37:06,600 --> 00:37:09,558
Show me Her Majesty's sheets
every morning.

307
00:37:09,640 --> 00:37:14,589
- l must know all her proper functions.
- Proper functions, Sir William ?

308
00:37:14,680 --> 00:37:16,636
lndeed.

309
00:37:18,720 --> 00:37:23,840
Her Majesty's body and person
are no longer her own property.

310
00:37:23,920 --> 00:37:25,956
They belong to the State.

311
00:37:26,040 --> 00:37:27,996
Yes, Sir William.

312
00:39:12,720 --> 00:39:14,233
Your Grace.

313
00:39:14,320 --> 00:39:16,595
Your Grace, Her Majesty has not risen.

314
00:39:16,680 --> 00:39:18,432
Your Grace !

315
00:39:18,960 --> 00:39:23,238
Please ! Your Grace ! Her Majesty
is not yet ready to receive visitors.

316
00:39:23,320 --> 00:39:25,072
Madam !

317
00:39:27,680 --> 00:39:30,831
You had best get up.
There is some grave news.

318
00:39:35,920 --> 00:39:37,876
My Lady, l'm sorry...

319
00:39:37,960 --> 00:39:42,556
Mary of Guise has increased the French
garrison in Scotland by 4,000 men.

320
00:39:42,640 --> 00:39:45,029
Perhaps more.

321
00:39:45,120 --> 00:39:46,599
Madam...

322
00:39:46,680 --> 00:39:51,037
l'm afraid the French mean to attack
while we are still weak

323
00:39:51,120 --> 00:39:54,556
and while Your Majesty's reign
is still uncertain.

324
00:39:57,480 --> 00:39:59,436
What is your counsel ?

325
00:39:59,520 --> 00:40:04,150
Madam, we must with all haste
raise an army to march upon Scotland.

326
00:40:08,760 --> 00:40:10,716
Can... can... ?

327
00:40:14,600 --> 00:40:16,556
Can we not send emissaries ?

328
00:40:16,640 --> 00:40:20,838
There is no time for that !
As Queen we look to you for action,

329
00:40:20,920 --> 00:40:26,597
unless you are content to wait for the
French to send more reinforcements.

330
00:40:26,680 --> 00:40:28,079
Here.

331
00:40:42,360 --> 00:40:44,316
Are you all in agreement ?

332
00:40:44,400 --> 00:40:49,235
l say there has never been a better time
to abate the French pride.

333
00:40:49,320 --> 00:40:50,275
Arundel ?

334
00:40:51,200 --> 00:40:55,159
War is a sin,
but sometimes a necessary one.

335
00:40:58,800 --> 00:41:03,749
Lord Robert, you were appointed to the
Council to protect England's interests.

336
00:41:03,840 --> 00:41:06,798
Now it appears
you do not have the stomach for it.

337
00:41:06,880 --> 00:41:08,632
l am in agreement, Your Grace,

338
00:41:08,720 --> 00:41:13,316
ifYour Majesty's throne is at risk.

339
00:41:20,640 --> 00:41:23,837
- What say you, Walsingham ?
- Your Majesty !

340
00:41:23,920 --> 00:41:27,117
l say a prince should rather
be slow to take action

341
00:41:27,200 --> 00:41:32,558
and should watch that he does not
come to be afraid of his own shadow.

342
00:41:32,640 --> 00:41:36,758
You are not, Sir Francis,
a member of Council,

343
00:41:36,840 --> 00:41:38,751
nor are you in the majority.

344
00:41:40,680 --> 00:41:42,636
l do not like wars.

345
00:41:43,920 --> 00:41:46,275
They have uncertain outcomes.

346
00:43:28,720 --> 00:43:32,554
SCOTLAND

347
00:44:03,280 --> 00:44:04,599
Stop !

348
00:44:38,000 --> 00:44:40,150
Go back to England,

349
00:44:40,240 --> 00:44:42,629
and take this to your Queen.

350
00:44:44,840 --> 00:44:47,593
English blood on French colours.

351
00:44:48,800 --> 00:44:51,598
Send him back to his Queen

352
00:44:51,680 --> 00:44:56,117
and make sure he remains alive.

353
00:44:58,000 --> 00:45:03,028
Tell that bastard Queen not to send
children to fight Mary of Guise !

354
00:45:12,800 --> 00:45:16,076
- Where are my councillors ?
- l know not, Madam.

355
00:45:16,160 --> 00:45:20,551
- Where is Lord Robert ?
- Lord Robert, Madam, has gone hunting.

356
00:45:25,160 --> 00:45:27,116
Leave me.

357
00:45:27,200 --> 00:45:29,156
Go ! Go !

358
00:45:33,080 --> 00:45:37,790
l regret to inform Your Majesty
of our miserable defeat in Scotland.

359
00:45:37,880 --> 00:45:41,031
The Bishops still demand
Your Majesty's removal.

360
00:45:41,120 --> 00:45:43,998
They find support in every quarter.

361
00:45:45,160 --> 00:45:48,709
Alas, Madam,
we are come already to catastrophe.

362
00:46:21,400 --> 00:46:24,153
How dare you come into my presence !

363
00:46:27,080 --> 00:46:29,036
Why do you follow me here ?

364
00:46:29,120 --> 00:46:32,476
lt is my business
to protect Your Majesty

365
00:46:33,760 --> 00:46:35,716
against all things.

366
00:46:35,800 --> 00:46:39,679
l do not need protection.
l need to be left alone !

367
00:46:39,760 --> 00:46:41,716
Majesty...

368
00:46:42,680 --> 00:46:46,116
They should never have been
sent to Scotland.

369
00:46:48,360 --> 00:46:51,716
My father would not have made
such a mistake.

370
00:46:53,120 --> 00:46:55,588
l have been proved unfit to rule.

371
00:46:57,080 --> 00:47:01,039
That is what you all think,
is it not, Walsingham ?

372
00:47:01,120 --> 00:47:03,031
lt is not for me to judge you.

373
00:47:05,720 --> 00:47:10,840
Why did they send children ! Why
did they not send proper reinforcements !

374
00:47:10,920 --> 00:47:13,480
The Bishops would not let them.

375
00:47:13,560 --> 00:47:16,632
They spoke against it in the pulpits.

376
00:47:16,720 --> 00:47:20,872
Then... they are speaking
against their Queen.

377
00:47:20,960 --> 00:47:25,192
Madam, the Bishops are against you
and have no fear of you.

378
00:47:25,280 --> 00:47:27,840
They do not expect you to survive.

379
00:47:40,120 --> 00:47:42,076
My Lord ! The Queen !

380
00:48:04,400 --> 00:48:06,356
Where have you been ?

381
00:48:10,640 --> 00:48:12,596
You were not at Court.

382
00:48:15,000 --> 00:48:16,956
Majesty, Monsieur de Foix.

383
00:48:17,040 --> 00:48:18,996
Mary of Guise, Ma'am,

384
00:48:19,080 --> 00:48:23,232
promises to make no further threat
against Your Majesty, but

385
00:48:23,320 --> 00:48:25,276
on one condition.

386
00:48:25,680 --> 00:48:27,636
What condition ?

387
00:48:28,320 --> 00:48:33,872
That Your Majesty considers the proposal
of her nephew the Duke of Anjou.

388
00:48:41,800 --> 00:48:45,509
The Duke is most eager
to meet Your Majesty.

389
00:48:45,600 --> 00:48:48,558
He has heard a great deal of your beauty.

390
00:48:49,320 --> 00:48:54,189
For the love of God, Madam, let not
the care of your diseased estate

391
00:48:54,280 --> 00:48:57,078
hang in the balance any longer.

392
00:48:57,160 --> 00:49:01,517
ln marriage,
and in the production of an heir,

393
00:49:01,600 --> 00:49:04,200
lies your only surety.

394
00:49:04,200 --> 00:49:07,078
The Duke is also most... handsome.

395
00:49:18,240 --> 00:49:20,196
Very well.

396
00:49:22,160 --> 00:49:23,798
lnvite the Duke of Anjou.

397
00:49:25,240 --> 00:49:27,595
We shall see him in the flesh.

398
00:49:37,480 --> 00:49:39,436
Robert !

399
00:49:39,520 --> 00:49:44,036
The Duke will not take kindly
to a rival for his suit.

400
00:49:44,120 --> 00:49:47,795
He is a traitor,
and his father before him.

401
00:49:47,880 --> 00:49:52,590
Lord Robert's head
will end up on a spike,

402
00:49:52,680 --> 00:49:55,194
not on the pillow of a Queen.

403
00:50:07,440 --> 00:50:09,396
Must you leave ?

404
00:50:09,480 --> 00:50:12,233
l would not miss this for the world.

405
00:50:13,120 --> 00:50:17,079
Today l shall watch the fall
of that heretic girl.

406
00:50:20,680 --> 00:50:24,639
l have been placed here
as your sov...

407
00:50:30,200 --> 00:50:33,476
l am your sovereign.
l have been placed here...

408
00:50:36,080 --> 00:50:37,718
l...

409
00:50:37,800 --> 00:50:41,031
God has... God has placed me here...

410
00:50:41,120 --> 00:50:43,793
l am your anointed sovereign...

411
00:50:43,880 --> 00:50:47,190
l am your Queen...
And like my father l mean to rule.

412
00:50:47,280 --> 00:50:51,990
There is one thing higher than royalty,
my Lords, and that

413
00:50:52,960 --> 00:50:54,916
is religion.

414
00:50:56,160 --> 00:50:58,151
l pass this... l pass this Act of...

415
00:50:58,240 --> 00:51:00,071
l ask you to pa... l...

416
00:51:00,160 --> 00:51:03,118
l ask you to pass this Act of Uniformity.

417
00:51:03,200 --> 00:51:04,997
Not for myself. For my people.

418
00:51:07,240 --> 00:51:09,196
They're my people...

419
00:51:09,800 --> 00:51:13,110
There is one God. We have
a common... There is one God.

420
00:51:14,680 --> 00:51:17,956
This is for my people.
My people are my care.

421
00:51:18,040 --> 00:51:19,996
The only care.

422
00:51:20,080 --> 00:51:23,390
My Lords, your votes are nothing
without my consent.

423
00:51:36,720 --> 00:51:42,511
lf there is no uniformity
of religious belief here

424
00:51:42,600 --> 00:51:46,957
then there can only be fragmentation.

425
00:51:48,840 --> 00:51:50,796
Disputes and quarrels.

426
00:51:52,960 --> 00:51:58,717
Surely, my Lords, it is better
to have a single Church of England.

427
00:52:08,000 --> 00:52:10,719
A single Church of England !

428
00:52:10,800 --> 00:52:13,234
With a common prayer book.

429
00:52:13,320 --> 00:52:15,276
And... and a...

430
00:52:17,680 --> 00:52:20,592
And... a common purpose.

431
00:52:25,360 --> 00:52:28,352
l ask you to pass
this Act of Uniformity

432
00:52:28,440 --> 00:52:30,829
not... not for myself

433
00:52:32,800 --> 00:52:35,553
but for my people

434
00:52:37,760 --> 00:52:40,513
who are my only care.

435
00:52:40,760 --> 00:52:42,716
Madam, by this Act,

436
00:52:43,160 --> 00:52:47,711
you force us to relinquish
our allegiance to the Holy Father.

437
00:52:47,800 --> 00:52:50,439
Hear, hear !

438
00:52:52,440 --> 00:52:54,829
How can l force you, Your Grace ?

439
00:52:54,920 --> 00:52:56,876
l am a woman.

440
00:52:59,760 --> 00:53:04,117
l have no desire
to make windows into men's souls.

441
00:53:06,120 --> 00:53:08,076
l simply ask

442
00:53:09,240 --> 00:53:11,196
can any man, in truth,

443
00:53:12,800 --> 00:53:14,950
serve two masters

444
00:53:15,040 --> 00:53:17,634
and be faithful to both ?

445
00:53:17,720 --> 00:53:19,836
Madam, this is heresy !

446
00:53:19,920 --> 00:53:22,514
No, Your Grace, this is

447
00:53:22,600 --> 00:53:24,556
common sense.

448
00:53:24,640 --> 00:53:27,598
Which is a most English virtue.

449
00:53:30,440 --> 00:53:33,193
Where is Gardiner ?
Where are the others ?

450
00:53:33,280 --> 00:53:34,713
Let us out !

451
00:53:34,800 --> 00:53:36,756
Open the door !

452
00:53:39,360 --> 00:53:41,954
This is Walsingham's doing.

453
00:53:42,280 --> 00:53:44,236
lt is the devil's work.

454
00:53:44,320 --> 00:53:46,880
lt will not serve her in any case.

455
00:53:47,400 --> 00:53:51,996
The Bishops will pass no measure
which severs us from Rome.

456
00:53:54,840 --> 00:53:58,719
Your Majesty would improve
all these matters

457
00:53:58,800 --> 00:54:00,995
if you would agree to marry.

458
00:54:01,080 --> 00:54:03,036
Aye. Marry, Madam.

459
00:54:03,840 --> 00:54:07,799
Aye. But marry who, Your Grace ?

460
00:54:08,720 --> 00:54:11,473
Will you give me some suggestion ?

461
00:54:12,760 --> 00:54:16,719
For some say France,
and others Spain, and

462
00:54:16,840 --> 00:54:20,116
and some cannot abide foreigners at all.

463
00:54:20,200 --> 00:54:25,115
So l'm not sure how best to please you
unless l married one of each.

464
00:54:29,880 --> 00:54:33,793
Now Your Majesty does make fun
of the sanctity of marriage.

465
00:54:33,880 --> 00:54:38,396
l do not think you should lecture me
on that, my Lord,

466
00:54:38,480 --> 00:54:42,439
since you yourself
have been twice divorced.

467
00:54:42,520 --> 00:54:45,432
And are now upon your third wife !

468
00:54:51,560 --> 00:54:55,519
Each of you must vote
according to your conscience.

469
00:54:57,360 --> 00:54:59,316
But remember this.

470
00:55:00,440 --> 00:55:02,590
ln your hands,

471
00:55:03,440 --> 00:55:05,590
upon this moment,

472
00:55:06,520 --> 00:55:10,479
lies the future happiness of my people,

473
00:55:10,560 --> 00:55:12,755
and the peace

474
00:55:12,840 --> 00:55:14,796
of this realm.

475
00:55:16,520 --> 00:55:20,752
Let that be upon your conscience also.

476
00:55:27,160 --> 00:55:29,754
My Lords, the House will divide.

477
00:55:38,600 --> 00:55:40,556
Walsingham... !

478
00:55:40,640 --> 00:55:44,952
l would know on what authority
you have kept us locked up here.

479
00:55:45,040 --> 00:55:48,828
Your Graces must forgive me,
but you are now free to go.

480
00:55:48,920 --> 00:55:53,277
l am sure this infernal work
has not saved your bastard Queen.

481
00:55:54,640 --> 00:55:57,279
Her Majesty... has won the argument.

482
00:55:58,280 --> 00:56:00,236
By what count ?

483
00:56:01,120 --> 00:56:03,588
By five, Your Grace.

484
00:56:05,200 --> 00:56:07,156
Five.

485
00:56:08,920 --> 00:56:11,115
You will be damned for this !

486
00:56:11,200 --> 00:56:15,159
And l pray God your wretched soul
will burn in hell !

487
00:56:54,320 --> 00:56:56,914
Report back to me at break of day.

488
00:57:40,040 --> 00:57:42,156
Enchanté.

489
00:57:46,160 --> 00:57:46,990
No !

490
00:57:47,080 --> 00:57:50,436
Because... l am Anjou !

491
00:57:53,280 --> 00:57:56,033
Yes, l am Anjou, yes ! l am Anjou.

492
00:58:00,320 --> 00:58:02,436
My God ! She loves it !

493
00:58:09,680 --> 00:58:11,636
And l can't wait...

494
00:58:11,720 --> 00:58:16,271
l dream of the moment
when we are naked together in bed

495
00:58:16,360 --> 00:58:19,909
where l can stroke your thigh
and perhaps even

496
00:58:20,000 --> 00:58:21,991
your quinny ?

